"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-pdf\"></use></svg>Download PDF</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportTopicButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2530512\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2530512\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 04, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104oau1665702896544.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/oau1665702896544.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/oau1665702896544.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"oau1665702896544\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      soap_rel_buf\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Releases the buffer used for the amended SOAP envelope buffer or clears the context area, if dynamic memory allocation is used.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"oau1665702896544__topic_d37895e1_d37896e1_d37897e1\">\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">#include &lt;wsciapi.h&gt;\nsoap_rel_buf(int which, void *buf, void *context)\n</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"oau1665702896544__section_xxv_vss_pcc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d134400e57\">Parameters</h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"oau1665702896544__ul_v2r_wss_pcc\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"oau1665702896544__li_d19202e1_d19203e1_d19204e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"oau1665702896544__p_d37901e1_d37902e1_d37903e1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">int which</code>—flag that identifies the\n            buffer to be released. An <code class=\"ph codeph\">enum</code> provided in the header file defines the\n            available values:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"oau1665702896544__ul_x2r_wss_pcc\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"oau1665702896544__li_d19205e1_d19206e1_d19207e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"oau1665702896544__p_d37904e1_d37905e1_d37906e1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">WSCIAPI_OUTBUF</code>—actual value ‘0’,\n                the buffer used for the amended SOAP envelope</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"oau1665702896544__li_d19208e1_d19209e1_d19210e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"oau1665702896544__p_d37907e1_d37908e1_d37909e1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">WSCIAPI_CONTEXT</code>—actual value\n                ‘1’, the context area</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"oau1665702896544__li_d19211e1_d19212e1_d19213e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"oau1665702896544__p_d37910e1_d37911e1_d37912e1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">void *buf</code>—pointer to the buffer that\n            is to be deallocated. This will be equal to the pointer returned in\n              <code class=\"ph codeph\">*out</code> by either the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">soap_pre_request()</span> or\n              <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">soap_post_request()</span> function if the <code class=\"ph codeph\">which</code>\n            parameter has the value <code class=\"ph codeph\">WSCIAPI_OUTBUF</code>, or it will be equal to the\n            pointer returned in <code class=\"ph codeph\">*context</code> if the <code class=\"ph codeph\">which</code> parameter\n            has the value <code class=\"ph codeph\">WSCIAPI_CONTEXT</code>.</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"oau1665702896544__li_d19214e1_d19215e1_d19216e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"oau1665702896544__p_d37913e1_d37914e1_d37915e1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">void *context</code>—pointer to the context\n            area that the implementation previously returned through either the\n              <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">soap_pre_request()</span> or <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">soap_post_request()</span>\n            function. Take care not to access memory through this pointer when the memory has been\n            freed by using the <code class=\"ph codeph\">buf</code> parameter. Both pointers point to the same\n            memory when the <code class=\"ph codeph\">which</code> parameter contains\n              <code class=\"ph codeph\">WSCIAPI_CONTEXT</code>.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"oau1665702896544__section_qjr_xss_pcc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d134400e152\">Return Values</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"oau1665702896544__p_d78386e1_d78387e1_d78388e1\">None</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"oau1665702896544__section_jnb_zss_pcc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d134400e161\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"oau1665702896544__p_d37925e1_d37926e1_d37927e1\">The function <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">soap_rel_buf()</span> is\n        intended to provide flexibility in terms of memory allocation and deallocation. An\n        implementation can allocate a block of memory, the context, which will be returned on every\n        subsequent call of the API functions. This can be useful for the implementation to store\n        data between calls or to implement efficient memory management for the amended SOAP\n        envelopes.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"oau1665702896544__p_d37928e1_d37929e1_d37930e1\">This function should be provided if dynamic memory\n        allocation is used, either for the amended SOAP envelope buffer or for the context area. It\n        is the implementation’s responsibility to free all allocated memory.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"oau1665702896544__p_d37931e1_d37932e1_d37933e1\">Uniface calls this function whenever:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"oau1665702896544__ul_wdd_1ts_pcc\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"oau1665702896544__li_d19217e1_d19218e1_d19219e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"oau1665702896544__p_d37934e1_d37935e1_d37936e1\">Uniface no longer needs the amended SOAP envelope,\n            that is, after a call to <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">soap_pre_request()</span> or\n              <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">soap_post_request()</span> and before the next call to either\n            function.</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"oau1665702896544__li_d19220e1_d19221e1_d19222e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"oau1665702896544__p_d37937e1_d37938e1_d37939e1\">Uniface exits, if a context area was allocated this\n            function</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2530512\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2530512\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "soap_rel_buf Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 04, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 soap_rel_buf Releases the buffer used for the amended SOAP envelope buffer or clears the context area, if dynamic memory allocation is used. #include <wsciapi.h> soap_rel_buf(int which, void *buf, void *context) Copy Parameters int which —flag that identifies the buffer to be released. An enum provided in the header file defines the available values: WSCIAPI_OUTBUF —actual value ‘0’, the buffer used for the amended SOAP envelope WSCIAPI_CONTEXT —actual value ‘1’, the context area void *buf —pointer to the buffer that is to be deallocated. This will be equal to the pointer returned in *out by either the soap_pre_request() or soap_post_request() function if the which parameter has the value WSCIAPI_OUTBUF , or it will be equal to the pointer returned in *context if the which parameter has the value WSCIAPI_CONTEXT . void *context —pointer to the context area that the implementation previously returned through either the soap_pre_request() or soap_post_request() function. Take care not to access memory through this pointer when the memory has been freed by using the buf parameter. Both pointers point to the same memory when the which parameter contains WSCIAPI_CONTEXT . Return Values None Description The function soap_rel_buf() is intended to provide flexibility in terms of memory allocation and deallocation. An implementation can allocate a block of memory, the context, which will be returned on every subsequent call of the API functions. This can be useful for the implementation to store data between calls or to implement efficient memory management for the amended SOAP envelopes. This function should be provided if dynamic memory allocation is used, either for the amended SOAP envelope buffer or for the context area. It is the implementation’s responsibility to free all allocated memory. Uniface calls this function whenever: Uniface no longer needs the amended SOAP envelope, that is, after a call to soap_pre_request() or soap_post_request() and before the next call to either function. Uniface exits, if a context area was allocated this function Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}